  "prompt": "Why is Quora eliminating topic-based moderation?",
  "response": "In April 2021, Quora announced that it would be discontinuing its topic-based moderation system. This decision was made as part of a broader effort to streamline the platform and improve the consistency of moderation practices. Here are a few key reasons behind this move:\n\n1. **Consistency and Efficiency**: Topic-based moderation led to inconsistencies because different topics might have different moderation standards. By centralizing moderation, Quora aims to apply uniform standards across the entire platform, leading to a more consistent user experience.\n\n2. **Resource Optimization**: Managing a large number of topic-based moderation teams can be resource-intensive. By eliminating this system, Quora reduces complexity and administrative overhead.\n\n3. **Improved Technology**: With advancements in AI and machine learning, Quora has been focusing on using automated systems to detect and manage content that violates their policies. These technologies can often handle moderation more swiftly and efficiently than human moderators working within specific topics.\n\n4. **Community Feedback**: Quora likely received feedback from users who experienced frustration with the previous moderation system. A centralized approach simplifies the process for users, making it easier to understand what content is allowed on the platform.\n\n5. **Scalability**: As Quora continues to grow, scaling a topic-based moderation system becomes increasingly challenging. A centralized system is more scalable and easier to manage as the platform expands.\n\nBy moving away from topic-based moderation, Quora hopes to create a more streamlined and effective moderation strategy that enhances the overall user experience.",
